description:
Peter David's 100-plus-issue run on INCREDIBLE HULK remains one of the character's most popular periods. Now, see how it all began in David's first string of Hulk stories as the gray-skinned goliath – or is that the sardonic strongman? – leaps into action against horrors from the grave, the stars and the house next door! Featuring the revitalization of one of the Hulk's longtime foes, the Leader! Guest-starring the original X-Men!

Collects INCREDIBLE HULK #331-339.
name: Volume 1

description: When the Hulk came back from the Crossroads, John Byrne was waiting for him - complementing his popular X-Men and FF runs by literally breaking the Green Goliath in two! After the Hulk and Bruce Banner are separated, the Jade Giant becomes the Earth's emerald enemy - outfighting Iron Man, Wonder Man, Sub-Mariner, Hercules and Doc Samson! Could the one to succeed where these powerhouses failed be...Bruce Banner himself?! Plus: the wedding of Bruce Banner and Betty Ross! The new Hulkbusters! And the sinister Scourge! Collecting INCREDIBLE HULK #314-319 AND ANNUAL #14, and MARVEL FANFARE #29.
name: Volume 1
Natale! Anche i Maiali Sono Più Buoni!

description: *COVER NEEDS TO BE REPLACED - FREE GIFT ATTACHED*
Lester tries to stop his life story being made into a sleazy action thriller.
name: Girls: The Movie

description: Lester is conned by reporter Maxi Scoops and producer Solly Greenblat into playing himself in the movie version of his own life.
name: Glamour Girls

description: Lester trys to live a normal life but it looks like the people of Dullsville don't share his dream.
name: The Girls Next Time

description: While hunting for jewels with the newly reformed Lizard Lady Lester enconters his boyhood flame, Brett Ashley.
name: And For Girls, Too, A Bell Shall Toll

description: Lester's old nemesis, former pirate queen the Lizard Lady, convinces him to travel to Spain to recover some jewels so that she can forsake crime forever and share Lester's dreams.
name: Girls in Love

description:
While searching for Maxi Scoops in the Bayou Lester makes a startling discovery about his father.

Also includes the back-up story "When Lester Went Through Puberty".
name: Two Goats For Sister Girls

description:
Lester and Apache go in search of Maxi Scoops who's gone missing in the Bayou, but the boys get more than they bargained for when Lester's nephews 
stowaway on the trip.
name: Born To Be Girls

description: Lester trys to live the perfect  mundane existence , but not all is as it seems.
name: Girls Out of Joint

description:
Maxi Scoops goes in search of the story behind Lester Girls.
 
Also included is the back-up story "Little Scoops: The Adventures of Maxi When She Was a Girl".
name: She Scoops To Conquer

description: In this prequel story to A Song of Ice and Fire, night falls over the life on one noble knight and brings the dawn of his squire's knighthood. Dubbing himself "Ser Duncan the Tall", The Hedge Knight sets forth to the tourney at Ashford Meadow in search of fame and glory and the honor of upholding his oath as a knight of the Seven Kingdoms. Unfortunately for him, the world isn't ready for a knight who keeps his oaths, and his chivalrous methods could be the very cause of his demise.
name: Chapter 5

volume.name: George R.R. Martin's The Hedge Knight

description: Both Lester and Maxi go undercover to escape their lives and inadvertently  run in to each other.
name: A New Girls!

description: Lester, Apache and Maxi discover a mysterious lost city in a Central American jungle, but instead of Mayans they find a perfect reproduction of a classic 50's American small town.
name: The Lost City Girls: Part 2

description: In the realm of the Broken Kingdoms, an agent named the Eternal has stolen a sword that is the sacred symbol of the southern emperor's power and authority. But before he can return to the northern kingdom, he finds himself trapped in the town of Qi Akuto by the Imperial Dragons.
Maxi and Apache attempt to escape Springville, but can they do so without Lester?
name: The Lost City of Girls: Part 4

description: After discovering another trace of his long-missing father, Lester resumes reading his dad's diary.
name: From Girls To Eternity

description:
Lester and Maxi renew their love, but in their Leroy Gals and Minnie Leeds identities.
 
Back-up story "Love... Willie and Jerry Style.  Which follows Lesters nephews fighting over the attention of the new girl in school.
name: Mystery Girls

description:
Princess Lucinda Issue 0 is a giant sized stand alone comic book reintroduces the character Princess Lucinda as well as set the stage for the Princess Lucinda limited series.

The full color comic contains two stories featuring the precocious wicked witch-princess;

Toad you so: Ever wonder what toads do when they’re alone. Well in they discuss the goings on of the day including a certain princess who made them what they are today.

BWFF: When Lucinda teams up with original Witch Girl Annabelle Deville they turn the lives of mortals upside down.

The book also contains pin-ups by various artist, a preview of the Princess Lucinda limited series and character information.

Witch Girls tales issue 1 is a giant sized full color comic containing three stories that introduces new readers to the world of Witch Girls;

Story one brings together a group of unique magical friends who must band together to save a young witch that has yet to discover her powers.

Story two are reintroduced the Rosa the street smart witch girl from story one and her day at the Willow-Mistt school of magic

Story three has wicked princess Lucinda forced to do the one think she’s terrible out…be a hero to a young mortal.

Witch Girls Tales also contains Game information based on the stories for the Witch Girls Tales Drama Diaries game and pin ups by various artist.
name: Witch Girls Tales

description: Official adaptation of the DCAU home video animated movie, Batman: Sub-Zero.
name: Batman and Robin Adventures: Sub-Zero

volume.name: The Batman and Robin Adventures: Sub-Zero

description: Will Jacobs and Gerard Jones tell the tale of how they became Lester Girls biographers.
name: Comic Book Girls

description: In "Random Acts of Violence," the upcoming graphic novella published by Image Comics, co-writers Jimmy Palmiotti and Justin Gray of "Power Girl" fame are ditching the tights and grabbing a knife to slice and dice their way through the dangers of fiction and creation. According to the writers, the story focuses on comic book creators Ezra and Todd and their first major published work, a horror character called Slasherman. Success starts flowing like a river, but when that river turns bloody and people start dying in the midst of a signing tour, it becomes clear that Ezra and Todd's creation has taken on a life of its own.
Tick and Arthur are summon by a mysterious phone call to go to the small town of Blood Creek where they are challanged to a marathon game of Monopoly by the creepy Count Reggie!
name: Night of the Living Tick

description: The Tick is contacted by C-Spandex (a superhero cable TV network) and tries convince him to think that he will be the most marketable property ever!
name: C-Spandex

description: The Tick has landed a job as a galactic man-servant/janitor/herald for the Nigh-Omnipotus who hungers for more 'Earthly delights'! How can The Tick stop this menace and return home safely?
name: Living Together

description: The Tick encounters THE JUSTLY COMPENSATED LEAGUE OF SUPER-HERO a group of heroes who ask for payment for their good deeds! The Tick decides to join this group which leeds to disaster... of course.
name: The Justly Compensated League of Super-heroes!

description: The Tick (soon after the conclusion of the interplanetary games) is accidentally beamed into deep space far from his intended target Earth. He encounters a long lost spacetraveller who has a very unusual job for him!
name: Kind Pats & Banana Pellets

description: The Justice League is made up of the world's greatest heroes. Over the years, through feature movies, television programs, and various publications, these heroes have transcended the comic book genre to become pop cultural icons. JLA: SECRET ORIGINS is an amazing look back at how these characters originally gained their powers and abilities and became the legendary heroes that they now are. Featuring striking paintings by award-winning artist Alex Ross, this masterpiece contains the origins of some of DC's greatest heroes including Batman, Superman, Aquaman, Wonder Woman, Captain Marvel, Green Lantern and the Flash.
name: OGN

description:
Lester and Maxi have a romantic holiday together, but under their Leroy Gals and Minnie Leeds personas.   Will they continue lying to each other or will the truth come out?

Back-up story "When GIrls Come Marching Home Again".  Chester Girls settles back into life at home.

Final Issue.
name: Girls and Gals Together

description:
Lester is abducted by aliens.
 
Back-up story "When Les Met Ted and Alicia".
name: Close Encounters of the Girl Kind

description:
Lester and Apache decide to fight crime as the superhero duo Girl-Man and Dick-Boy.
 
Second feature "Little Girls: The Adventures of Lester When He Was a Boy" details Lester and Apache Dicks first adventure together.
name: Super Girls

description: Lester goes in search of Gloria Gaylord, the only person on earth who might have a clue as to his long lost dad's whereabouts.
name: The Girls of Sunset Boulevard
